10.1.1 This Agreement is binding upon a corporation or other entity that is not in a state of dissolution, liquidation, or any similar process under the laws of its state or jurisdiction of incorporation or formation;

10.1.2 The execution, delivery, and performance of this Agreement by such Party have been duly authorized by all necessary corporate action, but may require shareholder approval if stipulated by the Party's internal regulations or by any applicable law;

10.1.3 The consent, approval, order, authorization, registration, declaration, filing, or exemption by any Third Party or governmental entity is not required for the execution, delivery, and performance of this Agreement by such Party in connection with said actions;

10.1.4 This Agreement may be subject to limitations in its enforceability against such Party due to (a) applicable bankruptcy, insolvency, reorganization or other laws of general application relating to or affecting the enforcement of creditors’ rights generally and (b) the effect of rules of law governing the availability of equitable remedies;

10.1.5 The execution, delivery, and performance of this Agreement may potentially conflict with, or result in a violation of, or default under, or give rise to a right of termination, cancellation, or acceleration of any obligation that would result in the creation of an encumbrance upon any of the assets owned by such Party under, any material provision of Applicable Law, of such Party’s organizational documents, or of any agreement, judgment, injunction, order, decree, or other instrument binding on such Party or any assets owned by such Party; however, it is understood that such potential issues are the sole responsibility of said Party.

10.1.6 Such Party shall be responsible for complying with all material Applicable Laws relating to its activities under this Agreement, and any failure to do so shall not relieve the Party from its obligations under this Agreement unless expressly provided otherwise in writing by both Parties.
